  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Speak Up!</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Young people in rural areas of South Sudan who have missed out on school have no opportunities to learn to read or write or find out about issues important to their health and well-being. Education where it exists is usually only provided to primary level and infact there are only 50 trained secondary school teachers in the whole area. This means that many people have missed out on education. This project will offer around 15,000 people across 100 villages the chance to learn to read and write by attending classes, by listening to special radio broadcasts which accompany the teaching, and by being given books and materials to that they can practice on their own. The result will be that thousands of people will be able to read and write, this will increase their chances of finding work or going on to other education. At the very least, it will build their confidence and give them the skills they need in their day to day lives.</narrative>
  </description>
